    • Method Detail

      • setVerbose

        public static void setVerbose(boolean verbose)
        Toggles between a lot of output and little output.
        Parameters:
        verbose - If verbose is true, then complete information is printed, whether the tests passes or fails. If verbose is false, only failures are printed.

      • assertEquals

        public static void assertEquals(java.lang.String message,
                                boolean expected,
                                boolean actual)
        Each of the assertEquals methods tests whether the actual result equals the expected result. If it does, then the test passes, otherwise it fails. The only difference between these methods is the types of the parameters. All take a String message and two values of some other type to compare:
        Parameters:
        message - a message or description of the test
        expected - the correct, or expected, value
        actual - the actual value

      • assertEquals

                                int actual)

      • assertTrue

        public static void assertTrue(java.lang.String message,
                              boolean actual)
        Asserts that a given boolean must be true. The test fails if the boolean is not true.
        Parameters:
        message - The test message
        actual - The boolean value asserted to be true.

      • assertFalse

        public static void assertFalse(java.lang.String message,
                               boolean actual)
        Asserts that a given boolean must be false. The test fails if the boolean is not false (i.e. if it is true).
        Parameters:
        message - The test message
        actual - The boolean value asserted to be false.

      • testSection

        public static void testSection(java.lang.String sectionTitle)
        Prints a header for a section of tests.
        Parameters:
        sectionTitle - The header that should be printed.

      • startTests

        public static void startTests()
        Initializes the test suite. Should be called before running any tests, so that passes and fails are correctly tallied.

      • finishTests

        public static void finishTests()
        Prints out summary data at end of tests. Should be called after all the tests have run.
